Vague eyewitness reports take him to Grand Falls, Canada, but before he can fully even start his search, he runs into Ceri – an intriguing circus talent that seems to know more than is convenient about the past of the Winchester family. Telling himself it’s only for research, Dean starts spending time with him. Soon enough, he finds himself deeper in the situation that he thought he’d be comfortable with; but, as it turns ou t, it doesn’t take a prince to make him kneel.

summary: So it’s essentially canon that at least for two-three hundred years, if not longer, Aziraphale and Crowley have been hanging out...
body:
So it’s essentially canon that at least for two-three hundred years, if not longer, Aziraphale and Crowley have been hanging out in the UK? 

So, British-themed headcanons:

Aziraphale:

  • unironically listens to the Archers. He pretends he doesn’t know what’s happening, but Crowley asked him once, and he knows exactly what minor farming issues are going on, and who knows who and who fell off a roof ten years ago. As an aside, Crowley’s probably seen every episode of Eastenders and/or Corrie because it’s the best comedy on TV. Neither of them watch Hollyoaks.
  • OK let’s be honest, he listens to all those old-timey programmes on Radio 4: Just a Minute, Desert Island, the works
  •  doesn’t own a TV, but invites himself round to Crowley’s so he can watch Springwatch. They both watch the Bake Off. Crowley hates Strictly, but Aziraphale gushes over the costumes, so guess who wins that fight over the remote. 
  • shops at Waitrose
  • has a really soft spot for Scotch Eggs but will never admit it because he once told Crowley that Sausage Rolls were a bit naff and he knows he’ll get an earful for it. 

Crowley:

  • has won a Blue Peter badge before. He’s very proud of it. 
  •  I have a feeling he listens to the Kermode and Mayo film review on 5 Live.  He’d like their soft brand of snarking. 
  • When Broadchurch was first broadcast, like everyone else, he was betting on who the killer was.  He has never told Aziraphale this, because Aziraphale wouldn’t let him hear the end of it
  • was indirectly responsible for that Greggs christmas advent advert where the baby jesus was represented by a sausage roll.


Add your own headcanons!

summary: Rewrite the stars Crowley x reader
body:
Rewrite the stars Crowley x reader

This was the hardest thing I’ve ever had to do. I’ve been to heaven. I’ve been to hell. I’ve fought my way out of purgatory. All of that quite literally. But that all added up to nothing compared to what I had to say to to Crowley, down in the dusty warehouse we’d been meeting in.

“Crowley… we can’t do this. The Winchesters will kill you if the ever find out about us. I can’t… I’d rather know you’re alive than see you dead. And it’s not just the Winchesters. Your subjects wouldn’t like it either. My job is to put them back. They might try to turn on you. I’m sorry.” Fighting back tears, I turned to leave.

Crowley tried to stop me, and he called over to me.

“You know I want you

It’s not a secret I try to hide

I know you want me

So don’t keep saying our hands are tied

You claim it’s not in the cards

Fate is pulling you miles away

And out of reach from me

But you’re here in my heart

So who can stop me if I decide

That you’re my destiny?”

I pause. He runs over to me and takes my hand, trying to pull me into a dance, while I try (reluctantly) to leave.

“What if we rewrite the stars?

Say you were made to be mine

Nothing could keep us apart

You’d be the one I was meant to find

It’s up to you, and it’s up to me

No one can say what we get to be

So why don’t we rewrite the stars?

Maybe the world could be ours

Tonight.”

I pull away, and I’m a little mad. I’m doing this to protect him.

“You think it’s easy

You think I don’t want to run to you

But there are mountains

And there are doors that we can’t walk through

I know you’re wondering why

Because we’re able to be

Just you and me

Within these walls

But when we go outside

You’re going to wake up and see that it was hopeless after all.” He looks a bit crestfallen, but still determined, so I go on.

“No one can rewrite the stars

How can you say you’ll be mine?

Everything keeps us apart

And I’m not the one you were meant to find

It’s not up to you

It’s not up to me

When everyone tells us what we can be

How can we rewrite the stars?

Say that the world can be ours

Tonight”

I have to admit it. I do love him. So much. I want him. But I can’t have him. But I guess I can finish this dance.

All I want is to fly with you

All I want is to fall with you

So just give me all of you

It feels impossible (it’s not impossible)

Is it impossible?

Say that it’s possible

How do we rewrite the stars?

Say you were made to be mine?

Nothing can keep us apart

‘Cause you are the one I was meant to find

It’s up to you

And it’s up to me

No one can say what we get to be

And why don’t we rewrite the stars?

Changing the world to be ours

The dance comes to a finish, and I have to go now, the longer I stay, the harder it will be.

“You know I want you

It’s not a secret I try to hide

But I can’t have you

We’re bound to break and my hands are tied.” I peck his cheek, and leave.

And few hours later, I’m drowning my sorrows in chocolate frosting and watching the greatest showman. The Winchesters saw me come in, and tried to get me to say what was wrong, but I brushed them off and came upstairs.

I must have dozed off, because the next thing I know, the movie is pretty much over, and the boys are coming in my room.

“What?” I ask.

“We just talked Crowley.” Sam started. Oh crap.

“Y/n/n, he’s hurting. Bad. I get why you thought this was better, but that’s love right there kiddo. Sam and I, we’ve had our hearts broken and lost love too many times. We don’t want you to go through that. If you want him, go get him. We’ll take care of any punk ass demon that gets ideas.” Dean smiles a little.

I half start bawling, half squeal, and throw my arms around them.

“I love you guys.” Then I go to get him.

“Wait a second.” Sam calls. “There’s chocolate like… everywhere… on your face.”
